 ST_HmiStatus
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 EVERYTHING the RPi HMI displays, packed into ONE struct so pyads can
 refresh the whole UI with a single read:
     plc.read_by_name('GVL_HMI.stStatus', structure_def=ST_HMI_STATUS)

 Direction: PLC -> Pi only. The Pi must never write this struct.
 pack_mode 1: byte-aligned, no padding — pyads structure_def matches 1:1.
=============================================================================]]></Comment><BitSize>1936</BitSize><SubItem><Name>nPlcHeartbeat</Name><Type>UDINT</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ increments every PLC cycle group; Pi checks it changes]]></Comment><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>0</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>nHmiHeartbeatEcho</Name><Type>UDINT</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ last heartbeat value received from Pi (debug aid)]]></Comment><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>32</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>bHmiOnline</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ PLC's view: Pi heartbeat is alive]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>64</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>eState</Name><Type>E_SystemState</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ current state (INT under the hood)]]></Comment><BitSize>16</BitSize><BitOffs>72</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>sStateName</Name><Type>STRING(31)</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ human-readable, e.g. 'SteamFlowing' (state pill)]]></Comment><BitSize>256</BitSize><BitOffs>88</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>bReady</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ green Ready dot (temps in band, no faults)]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>344</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>bAlarmActive</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ red Alarm dot (any fault bit set)]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>352</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>nActiveFaults</Name><Type>UINT</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ count of active fault bits (Alarms page stat card)]]></Comment><BitSize>16</BitSize><BitOffs>360</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>stProcess</Name><Type>ST_ProcessValues</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ pressures, temps, flow, water level]]></Comment><BitSize>392</BitSize><BitOffs>376</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>rFlowPercent</Name><Type>REAL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ rFlowActual / rFlowRated * 100 (bar graph)]]></Comment><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>768</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>arPidOutput</Name><Type>REAL</Type><ArrayInfo><LBound>1</LBound><Elements>6</Elements></ArrayInfo><Comment><![CDATA[ 1 dP, 2 SPA temp, 3 heater, 4 water, 5 FM temp, 6 spare]]></Comment><BitSize>192</BitSize><BitOffs>800</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>stFaults</Name><Type>ST_Faults</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ --- Faults --------------------------------------------------------------]]></Comment><BitSize>248</BitSize><BitOffs>992</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>rSetFlowApplied</Name><Type>REAL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ SLM]]></Comment><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>1240</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>rSetDsPressApplied</Name><Type>REAL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Torr]]></Comment><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>1272</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>rSetSpaTempApplied</Name><Type>REAL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ degC]]></Comment><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>1304</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>bMaintModeActive</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ TRUE while eState = Maintenance]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>1336</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>arValveState</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><ArrayInfo><LBound>1</LBound><Elements>4</Elements></ArrayInfo><Comment><![CDATA[ SV1 drain, SV2 main, SV3 process, SV4 water]]></Comment><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>1344</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>bLoopbackOn</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ legacy C31]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>1376</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>bDrainModeOn</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>1384</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>sPlcVersion</Name><Type>STRING(31)</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ version of the PLC program]]></Comment><BitSize>256</BitSize><BitOffs>1392</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>sHmiVersion</Name><Type>STRING(31)</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ echoed from Pi at startup, shown for record]]></Comment><BitSize>256</BitSize><BitOffs>1648</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>nUptimeSeconds</Name><Type>UDINT</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>1904</BitOffs></SubItem><Properties><Property><Name>pack_mode</Name><Value>1</Value></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name>ST_HmiCommand</Name><Comment><![CDATA[=============================================================================
 ST_HmiCommand
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Direction: Pi -> PLC. Consume-on-read pattern:
   * Pi writes TRUE to a command bit (pyads write_by_name).
   * FB_Hmi latches it into its outputs for exactly one PLC cycle,
     then writes FALSE back. The Pi never needs to clear anything.

=============================================================================]]></Comment><BitSize>160</BitSize><SubItem><Name>nHmiHeartbeat</Name><Type>UDINT</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Pi increments each poll cycle; never reset]]></Comment><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>0</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>bSesOn</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ start command]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>32</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>bSesOff</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ stop command ]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>40</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>bFaultReset</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ reset all faults]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>48</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>bFaultAck</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ acknowledge (silences banner, faults stay listed)]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>56</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>bEnterMaint</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ request Maintenance state]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>64</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>bExitMaint</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ leave Maintenance ]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>72</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>aValveCmd</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><ArrayInfo><LBound>1</LBound><Elements>4</Elements></ArrayInfo><Comment><![CDATA[ SV1 drain, SV2 main, SV3 process, SV4 water]]></Comment><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>80</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>bLoopbackOn</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ legacy C31 loopback mode]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>112</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>bDrainMode</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ drain mode]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>120</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>bDpControlOff</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ suspend diff pressure control]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>128</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>bTempControlOff</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ suspend purifier temp control]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>136</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>bExtHeaterEnable</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ external heater enable]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>144</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>bApplySetpoints</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ pulse: validate + apply stSetpointRequest]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>152</BitOffs></SubItem><Properties><Property><Name>pack_mode</Name><Value>1</Value></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name>ST_HmiSetpoints</Name><Comment><![CDATA[=============================================================================
 ST_HmiSetpoints
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Direction: Pi -> PLC (request) and PLC -> Pi (applied echo in ST_HmiStatus).
 Pi writes the whole struct, then pulses stCommand.bApplySetpoints.
 FB_Hmi clamps each value to ST_SetpointLimits before applying, and the
 clamped result is echoed in ST_HmiStatus.rSet*Applied so the UI always
 shows the truth, not the request.
=============================================================================]]></Comment><BitSize>96</BitSize><SubItem><Name>rSetFlow</Name><Type>REAL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ requested flow setpoint      [SLM]]]></Comment><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>0</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>rSetDsPressure</Name><Type>REAL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ downstream pressure setpoint [Torr]]]></Comment><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>32</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>rSetSpaTemp</Name><Type>REAL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ SPA temperature setpoint     [degC]]]></Comment><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>64</BitOffs></SubItem><Properties><Property><Name>pack_mode</Name><Value>1</Value></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name GUID="{302277DD-5AD1-433D-B776-5031AECC2BB4}" TcBaseType="true">EPlcPersistentStatus</Name><BitSize>8</BitSize><BaseType GUID="{18071995-0000-0000-0000-000000000002}">USINT</BaseType><EnumInfo><Text><![CDATA[PS_None]]></Text><Enum>0</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text><![CDATA[PS_All]]></Text><Enum>1</Enum></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text><![CDATA[PS_Partial]]></Text><Enum>2</Enum></EnumInfo><Hides><Hide GUID="{4591E628-DBCE-4E33-AE0B-7EB853AA256E}" /></Hides></DataType><DataType><Name GUID="{D8713831-B59F-4201-84CC-04357A7EE4B7}" TcBaseType="true">PlcAppSystemInfo</Name><BitSize>2048</BitSize><SubItem><Name>ObjId</Name><Type GUID="{18071995-0000-0000-0000-00000000000F}">OTCID</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>0</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>TaskCnt</Name><Type GUID="{18071995-0000-0000-0000-000000000008}">UDINT</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>32</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>OnlineChangeCnt</Name><Type GUID="{18071995-0000-0000-0000-000000000008}">UDINT</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>64</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>Flags</Name><Type GUID="{18071995-0000-0000-0000-000000000007}">DWORD</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>96</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>AdsPort</Name><Type GUID="{18071995-0000-0000-0000-000000000005}">UINT</Type><BitSi